@N2660:  fetch the bit map
@N2662:  prep for 16 times around the loop
@N2664:  walk the segment table back to front
@N2665:  first table entry
@N2666:         td tmp_tabx
@N2667:  second table entry
@N2670:         td tmp_taby
@N2671:  third table entry
@N2672:  no op
@N2673:         ca 0
@N2674:  end of debug hack
@N2675:  branch if most significant bit is on
@N2677:  shift AC left by one bit
@N2704:         td tmp_tabx
@N2707:         td tmp_taby
@N2714:  bail out when count exhausted
@N2715:  the SI uses the AC to set Y coord
@N2717:  initialize vector gen with the y-coord in ACC
@N2720:  the RC uses AC to set X coord and mem address for the vector length
@N2724: ; Return from draw_16seg_char
@N2731:  *********************************************************************************************************/
